article.headline: North Dakota 72, Mayville State 54
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Patrick Mitchell had 14 points and nine rebounds as North Dakota cruised past Mayville State 72-54 on Wednesday night. Aaron Anderson and Troy Huff scored 13 points each and Brandon Brekke added 10 for the Fighting Sioux (6-8), who snapped a three-game losing streak. Gus Kueber, Matt Bauduin and Cody Coauette scored 14 points apiece to pace the Comets (7-7), an NAIA school. North Dakota held a 16-13 lead before putting together a 12-2 run that provided a 28-15 edge with 7:00 left in the first half, closing the spurt on a 3-pointer by Mitchell. Mayville State closed within 40-35 with 13:16 to go on three free throws by Kueber. But North Dakota responded with an 11-2 run, and the lead reached 21 late in the game. The Comets were outrebounded 43-24. North Dakota, playing its first home game in three weeks, raised its home record to 6-1.
